#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:5
msgid "Telnet Console"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:10
msgid ""
"Scrapy comes with a built-in telnet console for inspecting and controlling a "
"Scrapy running process. The telnet console is just a regular python shell "
"running inside the Scrapy process, so you can do literally anything from it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:14
msgid ""
"The telnet console is a :ref:`built-in Scrapy extension <topics-extensions-"
"ref>` which comes enabled by default, but you can also disable it if you "
"want. For more information about the extension itself see :ref:`topics-"
"extensions-ref-telnetconsole`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:22
msgid "How to access the telnet console"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:24
msgid ""
"The telnet console listens in the TCP port defined in the :setting:"
"`TELNETCONSOLE_PORT` setting, which defaults to ``6023``. To access the "
"console you need to type::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:28
msgid ""
"telnet localhost 6023\n"
">>>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/telnetconsole.rst:31
msgid ""
"You need the telnet program which comes installed by default in Windows, and "
"most Linux distros."
msgstr ""

